```kcl
appearance::rgb(@rgb: [number(_); 3]): string
```

Build a color from its red, green and blue components.
These must be between 0 and 255.

### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `rgb` | [`[number(_); 3]`](/docs/kcl-std/types/std-types-number) |  | Yes |

### Returns

[`string`](/docs/kcl-std/types/std-types-string) - A sequence of characters


### Examples

```kcl
startSketchOn(-XZ)
  |> circle(center = [0, 0], radius = 10)
  |> extrude(length = 4)
  |> appearance(color = appearance::rgb([50, 160, 160]))
```

![Rendered example of appearance::rgb 0](data:image/png;base64,)

```kcl
sideLen = 30
n = 10

// The cubes become more green and less blue with each instance.
fn cube(i, center) {
  g = 255 / n * i
  b = 255 / n * (n - i)
  return startSketchOn(XY)
    |> polygon(radius = sideLen / 2, numSides = 4, center = [center, 0])
    |> extrude(length = sideLen)
    |> appearance(color = appearance::rgb([0, g, b]), metalness = 80, roughness = 20)
}

// Create n cubes, shifting each one over in a line.
map(
  [0..n],
  f = fn(@i) {
    return cube(i, center = sideLen * i * 1.5)
  },
)
```
